This paper is primarily focused on the design and analysis of combinatorial structures used in space-time block codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves some algebraic and number theoretic techniques, which could potentially place it in the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) or information theory and coding theory (cs.ITP). Additionally, the paper involves some computational aspects, which could place it in the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) or computational complexity (cs.CC).
